---
import LayoutRedesign from '../layouts/LayoutRedesign.astro';
const lastUpdated = 'January 19, 2025';
---

<LayoutRedesign title="Acceptable Use Policy - Intent Solutions">
  <!-- SECTION 1: Hero + Introduction (IMAGE BACKGROUND) -->
  <section class="acceptable-use-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <h1 class="hero-title">
          Acceptable <span class="highlight-box">Use</span> Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
        <p class="hero-description">
          This Acceptable Use Policy outlines prohibited activities when using Intent Solutions' services. By accessing our AI solutions, consulting services, or products, you agree to use them responsibly and lawfully.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 2: Main Policy Content (DARK BACKGROUND ONLY) -->
  <section class="policy-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="policy-text">

        <!-- Overview -->
        <h2>1. <span class="highlight-box">Overview</span></h2>
        <p>
          This Acceptable Use Policy ("Policy") governs your use of Intent Solutions' services, including our AI/ML consulting, software products, cloud infrastructure, and related offerings. This Policy is incorporated into our Terms of Service.
        </p>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to investigate any violation of this Policy and take appropriate action, including suspension or termination of services, removal of content, and reporting to law enforcement authorities.
        </p>

        <!-- Prohibited Activities -->
        <h2>2. <span class="highlight-box">Prohibited Activities</span></h2>
        <p>
          You may not use our Services to engage in, facilitate, or promote any of the following activities:
        </p>

        <h3>2.1 Illegal Activities</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Criminal Conduct:</strong> Any activity that violates federal, state, local, or international laws</li>
          <li><strong>Fraud:</strong> Deceptive practices, identity theft, phishing, or financial fraud</li>
          <li><strong>Intellectual Property Infringement:</strong> Copyright violation, trademark infringement, or unauthorized use of proprietary content</li>
          <li><strong>Unauthorized Access:</strong> Hacking, password cracking, or bypassing security measures</li>
          <li><strong>Distribution of Malware:</strong> Creating, distributing, or facilitating viruses, ransomware, or malicious code</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.2 Harmful Content</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Child Safety:</strong> Content exploiting or endangering minors in any way</li>
          <li><strong>Violence:</strong> Graphic violence, terrorism promotion, or content inciting harm</li>
          <li><strong>Hate Speech:</strong> Content promoting hatred, discrimination, or violence based on race, ethnicity, religion, gender, sexual orientation, disability, or other protected characteristics</li>
          <li><strong>Harassment:</strong> Threatening, bullying, stalking, or abusive behavior toward individuals or groups</li>
          <li><strong>Non-Consensual Content:</strong> Intimate images shared without consent, deepfakes, or unauthorized impersonation</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.3 Spam and Abuse</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Mass Unsolicited Communications:</strong> Sending spam emails, SMS, or other bulk messages</li>
          <li><strong>Automated Scraping:</strong> Using bots or automated tools to scrape data without authorization</li>
          <li><strong>Resource Abuse:</strong> Excessive API calls, denial-of-service attacks, or intentional service degradation</li>
          <li><strong>Fake Accounts:</strong> Creating multiple accounts for deceptive purposes or circumventing restrictions</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- AI-Specific Restrictions -->
        <h2>3. AI-Specific <span class="highlight-box">Restrictions</span></h2>
        <p>
          When using our AI services, including Claude Code plugins, custom AI agents, or AI infrastructure:
        </p>

        <h3>3.1 Model Misuse</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Jailbreaking:</strong> Attempting to bypass safety filters, content policies, or usage restrictions</li>
          <li><strong>Malicious Prompts:</strong> Crafting prompts designed to generate harmful, illegal, or dangerous content</li>
          <li><strong>Bias Amplification:</strong> Intentionally exploiting or amplifying model biases for harmful purposes</li>
          <li><strong>Misinformation:</strong> Using AI to generate misleading content, fake news, or manipulated media at scale</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.2 Unauthorized Usage</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Competing Products:</strong> Using our AI infrastructure to build direct competing products without authorization</li>
          <li><strong>Reverse Engineering:</strong> Attempting to extract model weights, training data, or proprietary algorithms</li>
          <li><strong>Benchmark Gaming:</strong> Manipulating benchmarks or performance metrics to misrepresent capabilities</li>
          <li><strong>Credential Theft:</strong> Using AI to generate phishing content, fake credentials, or social engineering attacks</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.3 Data Privacy Violations</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>PII Processing:</strong> Processing personally identifiable information without proper consent or legal basis</li>
          <li><strong>Training Data Misuse:</strong> Using customer data to train models without explicit permission</li>
          <li><strong>Data Exfiltration:</strong> Attempting to extract other users' data or system information</li>
          <li><strong>Cross-Tenant Access:</strong> Attempting to access data or resources from other customers</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Security and Infrastructure -->
        <h2>4. Security and <span class="highlight-box">Infrastructure</span></h2>
        <p>
          You must use our cloud infrastructure and services securely:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Security Testing:</strong> Do not perform penetration testing or vulnerability scanning without written permission</li>
          <li><strong>Network Attacks:</strong> No port scanning, DDoS attacks, or other network-based attacks</li>
          <li><strong>Credential Sharing:</strong> Do not share API keys, passwords, or access credentials</li>
          <li><strong>Encryption Requirements:</strong> Use encryption for sensitive data in transit and at rest</li>
          <li><strong>Vulnerability Disclosure:</strong> Report security vulnerabilities responsibly through proper channels</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Data Usage and Retention -->
        <h2>5. Data <span class="highlight-box">Usage</span> and Retention</h2>
        <p>
          When using our services, you must:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> Ensure all data usage complies with GDPR, CCPA, and other applicable privacy laws</li>
          <li><strong>Data Minimization:</strong> Collect and process only necessary data for your use case</li>
          <li><strong>User Consent:</strong> Obtain proper consent for data collection and processing</li>
          <li><strong>Retention Limits:</strong> Follow data retention policies and delete data when no longer needed</li>
          <li><strong>Third-Party Data:</strong> Respect third-party data rights and licensing agreements</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Rate Limits and Resource Usage -->
        <h2>6. Rate Limits and <span class="highlight-box">Resource Usage</span></h2>
        <p>
          To ensure fair usage for all customers:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>API Rate Limits:</strong> Respect published API rate limits and quotas</li>
          <li><strong>Compute Resources:</strong> Use compute resources efficiently and as specified in your plan</li>
          <li><strong>Storage Limits:</strong> Stay within allocated storage quotas</li>
          <li><strong>Bandwidth:</strong> Avoid excessive bandwidth consumption that impacts other users</li>
          <li><strong>Burst Traffic:</strong> Implement proper rate limiting and caching to avoid sudden traffic spikes</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Commercial Use Restrictions -->
        <h2>7. Commercial <span class="highlight-box">Use</span> Restrictions</h2>
        <p>
          For open-source tools and free-tier services:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Attribution:</strong> Provide proper attribution as required by open-source licenses</li>
          <li><strong>License Compliance:</strong> Follow MIT, Apache 2.0, or other applicable license terms</li>
          <li><strong>Free Tier Limits:</strong> Do not abuse free-tier services for commercial purposes beyond stated limits</li>
          <li><strong>Resale Restrictions:</strong> Do not resell access to our services without authorization</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Enforcement and Consequences -->
        <h2>8. <span class="highlight-box">Enforcement</span> and Consequences</h2>
        <p>
          Violations of this Policy may result in:
        </p>

        <h3>8.1 Immediate Actions</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Content Removal:</strong> Immediate removal of violating content or data</li>
          <li><strong>Service Suspension:</strong> Temporary suspension of account access pending investigation</li>
          <li><strong>Rate Limiting:</strong> Throttling or limiting API access for abuse</li>
          <li><strong>Account Termination:</strong> Permanent termination of services for serious violations</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>8.2 Legal Actions</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Law Enforcement:</strong> Reporting criminal activity to appropriate authorities</li>
          <li><strong>Civil Liability:</strong> Pursuing legal action for damages caused by violations</li>
          <li><strong>Third-Party Claims:</strong> Cooperation with third-party intellectual property or legal claims</li>
          <li><strong>Data Preservation:</strong> Preserving data for legal proceedings as required</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>8.3 No Refunds</h3>
        <p>
          Violations of this Policy may result in immediate termination without refund of any prepaid fees or subscription costs.
        </p>

        <!-- Reporting Violations -->
        <h2>9. Reporting <span class="highlight-box">Violations</span></h2>
        <p>
          If you become aware of any violations of this Policy:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact Us:</strong> Email <a href="mailto:jeremy@intentsolutions.io">jeremy@intentsolutions.io</a> with detailed information</li>
          <li><strong>Provide Evidence:</strong> Include URLs, screenshots, or other evidence of violations</li>
          <li><strong>Response Time:</strong> We will investigate and respond within 48 hours</li>
          <li><strong>Confidentiality:</strong> Reports are handled confidentially where possible</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Changes to This Policy -->
        <h2>10. Changes to This <span class="highlight-box">Policy</span></h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Acceptable Use Policy from time to time. Material changes will be communicated via:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email notification to registered users</li>
          <li>Prominent notice on our website</li>
          <li>In-app notification for significant changes</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Continued use of our Services after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated Policy.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 3: Reporting Contact (DARK + TEAL WAVE BACKGROUND) -->
  <section class="policy-contact">
    <!-- Teal wave background -->
    <div class="wave-background">
      <svg class="wave wave-1" viewBox="0 0 1440 320" preserveAspectRatio="none">
        <path fill="rgba(13, 148, 136, 0.3)" d="M0,192L48,197.3C96,203,192,213,288,229.3C384,245,480,267,576,250.7C672,235,768,181,864,181.3C960,181,1056,235,1152,234.7C1248,235,1344,181,1392,154.7L1440,128L1440,320L1392,320C1344,320,1248,320,1152,320C1056,320,960,320,864,320C768,320,672,320,576,320C480,320,384,320,288,320C192,320,96,320,48,320L0,320Z"></path>
      </svg>
      <svg class="wave wave-2" viewBox="0 0 1440 320" preserveAspectRatio="none">
        <path fill="rgba(20, 184, 166, 0.2)" d="M0,64L48,80C96,96,192,128,288,128C384,128,480,96,576,90.7C672,85,768,107,864,144C960,181,1056,235,1152,234.7C1248,235,1344,181,1392,154.7L1440,128L1440,320L1392,320C1344,320,1248,320,1152,320C1056,320,960,320,864,320C768,320,672,320,576,320C480,320,384,320,288,320C192,320,96,320,48,320L0,320Z"></path>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <div class="contact-content">
        <h2>Report Policy <span class="highlight-box">Violations</span></h2>
        <p>
          If you encounter content or behavior that violates this Acceptable Use Policy, please report it immediately.
        </p>
        <div class="contact-details">
          <div class="contact-item">
            <strong>Email:</strong>
            <a href="mailto:jeremy@intentsolutions.io">jeremy@intentsolutions.io</a>
          </div>
          <div class="contact-item">
            <strong>Response Time:</strong>
            <span>Within 48 hours</span>
          </div>
          <div class="contact-item">
            <strong>Include:</strong>
            <span>URLs, screenshots, and detailed description</span>
          </div>
          <div class="contact-item">
            <strong>Confidential:</strong>
            <span>Reports handled with discretion</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="legal-note">
          Thank you for helping us maintain a safe, secure, and lawful environment for all users.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</LayoutRedesign>

<style>
  /* ============================================
     SECTION 1: Hero + Introduction (IMAGE BACKGROUND)
     ============================================ */
  .acceptable-use-hero {
    position: relative;
    background:
      linear-gradient(
        to bottom,
        rgba(10, 15, 26, 0.88) 0%,
        rgba(10, 15, 26, 0.80) 100%
      ),
      url('/images/acceptable-use-bg.jpg') center/cover no-repeat;
    background-attachment: scroll, fixed;
    padding: 10rem 0 5rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hero-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-light);
  }

  .last-updated {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-accent-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .hero-description {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-light-muted);
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .acceptable-use-hero {
      padding: 8rem 0 4rem;
    }
  }

  /* ============================================
     SECTION 2: Main Policy Content (DARK BACKGROUND ONLY)
     ============================================ */
  .policy-content {
    background: var(--bg-dark);
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .policy-text {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .policy-text h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-light);
    margin-top: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(13, 148, 136, 0.3);
  }

  .policy-text h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .policy-text h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-light);
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .policy-text p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-light-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .policy-text ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .policy-text li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-light-muted);
    padding-left: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .policy-text li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.7em;
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    background: var(--color-accent-secondary);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .policy-text a {
    color: var(--color-accent-secondary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    transition: color var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .policy-text a:hover {
    color: #14b8a6;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .policy-content {
      padding: 3rem 0 4rem;
    }

    .policy-text h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .policy-text h3 {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
    }
  }

  /* ============================================
     SECTION 3: Reporting Contact (DARK + TEAL WAVE)
     ============================================ */
  .policy-contact {
    position: relative;
    background: var(--bg-dark);
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: 4rem 0 6rem;
  }

  /* Teal wave background */
  .wave-background {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 50%;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }

  .wave {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .wave-1 {
    animation: wave-float 20s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  .wave-2 {
    animation: wave-float 15s ease-in-out infinite reverse;
  }

  @keyframes wave-float {
    0%, 100% {
      transform: translateX(0) translateY(0);
    }
    50% {
      transform: translateX(-20px) translateY(10px);
    }
  }

  .contact-content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .contact-content h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-light);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .contact-content > p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-light-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .contact-details {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: rgba(13, 148, 136, 0.1);
    backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid rgba(13, 148, 136, 0.3);
  }

  .contact-item {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .contact-item strong {
    color: var(--text-light);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .contact-item span {
    color: var(--text-light-muted);
  }

  .contact-item a {
    color: var(--color-accent-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .contact-item a:hover {
    color: #14b8a6;
  }

  .legal-note {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .policy-contact {
      padding: 3rem 0;
    }

    .contact-content h2 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }

    .contact-details {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    .contact-item {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.25rem;
    }
  }

  /* ============================================
     Highlight Box (Lime)
     ============================================ */
  .highlight-box {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-highlight);
    color: var(--bg-dark);
    padding: 0.1em 0.3em;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  }

  /* Container */
  .container {
    max-width: var(--container-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }
</style>
